	"MD013": false, // <!-- custom: similarly some very long lines are valid in our code, generally for commented-out code but maybe not only (didn't check if there are exceptions), so show them as such -->
	"MD033": false // <!-- custom: similarly or also we use tags like <img src="./_1_AdvCiv-SAS/Images/advisors/0.516_technology_advisor (1).JPG" alt="0.516_technology_advisor (1).JPG" width="250"></img> raw in our .md readme files, as this is the only way i found to reduce image width to say 250px instead of full size, an image markdown insert like ![img_military_tree_1](/_1_AdvCiv-SAS/Images/misc_0.x/0.43%20military%20tree_modified.png) doesn't seem to provide such an option (to reduce size) or at least it doesn't seem functional, so until and if i ever find hopefully such an option, i am fine to keep it as is as this seems functional, so disable the markdownlint rule instead -->
